 MBOMBELA – The Mpumalanga Provincial Legislature office is the latest to temporary close its doors after a member of staff tested positive for Covid-19. A statement from the MPL read: “The legislature secretary, Linda Mwale, on the advice of the Covid-19 compliance officer, has since decided to close the office for decontamination”. ALSO READ: Nelspruit Police Station temporarily closed after positive Covid-19 case, services to resume tomorrow Normal businesses is expected to resume at the MPL next week Tuesday after the building has been decontaminated. “Members of the public who require any assistance from the legislature during this period can contact the office by sending a text message to 067-428-3345,” the statement concluded.  